<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870113-0135 </DOCNO><HL> Purolator's Plan to ShedIts Operations Advances</HL><DD> 01/13/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PCCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> BASKING RIDGE, N.J.  </DATELINE><TEXT>    Purolator Courier Corp. tookanother step in selling off its operations, as the sale ofits Canadian courier unit to Onex Capital Corp. was approvedby both companies' boards.   Purolator said it will post a gain on the $170 million (U.S.) sale to Onex, but wouldn't specify the size of the gain. Purolator said it expects to complete the sale by April 30. Onex is a closely held Toronto investment concern. Purolator had announced a definitive agreement on the Onex transaction late last month.    Arthur DeMelle, Purolator's executive vice president, finance, declined to say how the courier and auto-parts company is doing in its efforts to sell its other operations. In November, Purolator said it planned to dispose of its businesses &quot;on an orderly basis.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>